'break' terminates the loop entirely and exits it. 'continue' skips the rest of the current iteration and jumps to the next iteration.

Example:
```c
for(int i=1; i<=5; i++) {
    if(i==3) break;    // Loop stops at i=3
    printf("%d ", i);  // Output: 1 2
}

for(int i=1; i<=5; i++) {
    if(i==3) continue; // Skips i=3
    printf("%d ", i);  // Output: 1 2 4 5
}
```

