int power(int x, int n) {
    if(n == 0) return 1;
    return x * power(x, n-1);
}
```
Or more efficient (divide and conquer):
```c
int power(int x, int n) {
    if(n == 0) return 1;
    if(n % 2 == 0) return power(x*x, n/2);
    return x * power(x*x, n/2);
}
```

